# Teacher Assignment & Reporting System

## Goal

Build a teacher-centric assignment system where a teacher can teach **multiple subjects** across **multiple classes**, **divisions**, and **classrooms** — with full attendance reporting for both **teacher** and **admin** panels.

## Current State

| What Exists | Problem |
|---|---|
| `attendance.subject` is `varchar` | No relational link to teacher |
| `attendance_session` has `class_name`, `division` | No `teacher_id` FK |
| [attendance](file:///d:/A/Attendify-Sanika/Attendify-Sanika/register/src/main/java/com/example/attendance_Backend/repository/AttendanceRepository.java#36-46) has no `teacher_id` | Can't filter attendance by teacher |
| No `teacher_assignments` table | Can't define what a teacher teaches |

---

## Proposed Changes

### Database Layer

#### [NEW] `teacher_assignments` table

Links a teacher to their class + subject + division + room. This is the **core** of the system.

```sql
CREATE TABLE teacher_assignments (
    id INT PRIMARY KEY AUTO_INCREMENT,
    teacher_id INT NOT NULL,
    subject VARCHAR(100) NOT NULL,
    class_name VARCHAR(100) NOT NULL,
    division VARCHAR(10),
    room_number VARCHAR(50),
    FOREIGN KEY (teacher_id) REFERENCES teachers(id) ON DELETE CASCADE
);
```

#### [MODIFY] [attendance](file:///d:/A/Attendify-Sanika/Attendify-Sanika/register/src/main/java/com/example/attendance_Backend/repository/AttendanceRepository.java#36-46) table — add `teacher_id`

```sql
ALTER TABLE attendance
ADD COLUMN teacher_id INT,
ADD FOREIGN KEY (teacher_id) REFERENCES teachers(id);
```

#### [MODIFY] `attendance_session` table — add `teacher_id`

```sql
ALTER TABLE attendance_session
ADD COLUMN teacher_id INT,
ADD FOREIGN KEY (teacher_id) REFERENCES teachers(id);
```

