## How It All Connects

```mermaid
erDiagram
    TEACHERS ||--o{ TEACHER_ASSIGNMENTS : "teaches"
    TEACHER_ASSIGNMENTS }o--|| TEACHERS : "assigned_to"
    TEACHERS ||--o{ ATTENDANCE_SESSION : "creates"
    TEACHERS ||--o{ ATTENDANCE : "recorded_by"
    USERS ||--o{ ATTENDANCE : "marks"
    ATTENDANCE_SESSION ||--o{ ATTENDANCE : "via_session"

    TEACHERS {
        int id PK
        string name
        string email UK
        string department
    }
    TEACHER_ASSIGNMENTS {
        int id PK
        int teacher_id FK
        string subject
        string class_name
        string division
        string room_number
    }
    ATTENDANCE {
        int id PK
        int user_id FK
        int teacher_id FK
        string subject
        date date
        string status
    }
    ATTENDANCE_SESSION {
        string id PK
        int teacher_id FK
        string subject
        string class_name
        string division
    }
```

## Teacher Flow Example

> **Prof. Sharma** teaches Math to CSE-A, CSE-B, and Physics to MECH-A

1. Admin creates 3 `teacher_assignments` for Prof. Sharma
2. Prof. Sharma logs in → sees only CSE-A, CSE-B (Math), MECH-A (Physics)
3. Creates QR session for "Math, CSE-A" → `attendance_session.teacher_id = Sharma.id`
4. Students scan → `attendance.teacher_id = Sharma.id`
5. Prof. Sharma opens reports → filters by subject/class/division/date
6. Admin opens admin panel → sees Prof. Sharma's complete attendance stats

## Verification Plan

### Automated Tests
1. `mvn spring-boot:run` — verify clean startup with new entities
2. POST to `/api/teacher-assignments` — create assignment
3. GET `/api/teacher-assignments/teacher/{id}` — verify assignments returned
4. POST to `/api/attendance/mark` — verify `teacher_id` saved
5. GET `/api/reports/teacher/{id}/summary` — verify summary stats
6. GET `/api/admin/reports/all-teachers` — verify admin can see all teachers

### Manual Verification
- Login as teacher → verify filtered dashboard
- Login as admin → verify admin can see teacher reports
